## Call for Posters

<div class="call-intro">

We invite submissions of poster abstracts for the **IROS 2026 Workshop on Haptics and Dexterous Manipulation**.

The poster session will provide an informal forum where researchers can present ongoing work, emerging ideas, and recent results related to the integration of **haptics, tactile sensing, and dexterous robotic manipulation**.

The goal of this session is to foster discussion and collaboration between researchers working on the fundamental technologies enabling human-like dexterity in robotic systems.

</div>

---

## Topics of Interest

<div class="topics-box">

Relevant topics include, but are not limited to:

- Haptic feedback for robotic manipulation  
- Tactile sensing and perception  
- Bio-inspired tactile systems  
- Slip detection and tactile event sensing  
- Dexterous robotic manipulation  
- Control strategies for dexterous manipulation  
- Learning-based control for manipulation  
- Teleoperation and human-in-the-loop manipulation  
- Human tactile perception and psychophysics  
- Haptic interfaces and wearable haptics  
- Machine learning for tactile sensing  
- Applications of haptics in robotics, VR/AR, and telemanipulation  

</div>

---

## Submission Guidelines

Poster submissions should include:

**1. One-page abstract (PDF)**  

The abstract should contain:

- Title  
- Authors and affiliations  
- Brief description of the work  
- Optional figures illustrating the approach or results  

**2. Graphical summary (required)**  

Authors must also submit a **graphical summary** illustrating the key idea of the work.

This image will be used for:

- the poster listing on the workshop website  
- the digital poster booklet distributed to workshop participants  

The graphical summary should be provided as **PNG or JPG**.

